         <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn" rendition="class:83225 maturity:83209">
             <p><lb n="1"/>therāna bhayatamahārakhitāna Atevāsiniya <unclear>A</unclear>la<unclear>ka</unclear>nha<unclear>k</unclear>iciya <unclear>U</unclear>t<unclear>i</unclear>yāya mahācetiye d<unclear>e</unclear>yadhama</p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
             <listApp>
                 <app loc="1">
                     <lem>therāna bhayatamahārakhitāna</lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Nakanishi+Hinuber2014_01"><unclear>the</unclear><supplied reason="lost">rāna</supplied> <supplied reason="lost">bha</supplied><unclear>yata ma</unclear>hā<unclear>rakhitāna</unclear></rdg>
                 </app>
                 <app loc="1">
                     <lem>Atevāsiniya</lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Nakanishi+Hinuber2014_01">Atevāsinā<gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></rdg>
                 </app>
                 <app loc="1">
                     <lem><unclear>A</unclear>la<unclear>ka</unclear>nha<unclear>k</unclear>iciya</lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Nakanishi+Hinuber2014_01"><gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character"/>kācaya</rdg>
                     <note><foreign>-kici</foreign> may be here feminine form for <foreign>-kica</foreign>, a term attested in composition with what appear to be toponyms in the Amaravati corpus. See <ref target="DHARMA_INSEIAD00278.xml">EIAD 278</ref>, l. 1: <foreign>… <supplied reason="lost">ca</supplied>dakicasa gahapatisa kanhatiputasa …</foreign>; <ref target="DHARMA_INSEIAD00312">EIAD 312</ref>, l. 1-2: <foreign>chadākicasa sethipamukhasa bhadanigamasa</foreign>; <ref target="DHARMA_INSEIAD00350">EIAD 350</ref>, l. 1: <foreign>…tulakicasa gahapatisa kubulasa putasa …</foreign>. <bibl><ptr target="bib:Luders1912_01"/><citedRange unit="page">179</citedRange><citedRange unit="item">1205a</citedRange></bibl> renders the latter compound as <quote>inhabitant of <placeName>Tulaka</placeName></quote>.</note>
                 </app>
                 <app loc="1">
                     <lem><unclear>U</unclear>t<unclear>i</unclear>yāya</lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Nakanishi+Hinuber2014_01"><gap reason="lost" quantity="2" unit="character"/>taya<gap reason="lost" quantity="2" unit="character"/></rdg>
                 </app>
             </listApp>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" resp="part:vito">
             <p>The pious gift to the Great Shrine of Uttiyā, the inhabitant of Alakaṇha (?), a pupil of the venerable reverend <persName type="human">Mahārakkhita</persName>.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
             <p>Although not recognised by <bibl><ptr target="bib:Nakanishi+Hinuber2014_01"/></bibl>, this inscription very probably corresponds to <bibl><ptr target="bib:Poonacha2011_01"/><citedRange unit="item">222</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
         </div>
